  "question": "The company _______ (not / not / haven't) announced its new product line yet.",
  "difficulty": "hard",
  "reasoning": "The sentence is in the present perfect tense, specifically the negative form. The correct answer is \"haven't\" because it is the contracted form of \"have not\" and is the correct way to express a negative present perfect tense. \"Not\" is incorrect as it does not form the negative present perfect tense. The option \"not\" is also incorrect because it does not form the negative present perfect tense and the sentence requires an auxiliary verb. \"Haven't\" is the only option that correctly combines the auxiliary verb \"have\" with the negation \"not\" to form the negative present perfect tense."
}
